      <h1 class="page-header">2015 Summer Internship</h1>
      <p>Last summer, I worked at Splash as a Junior developer. Splash is a marketing software where you can create your own beautiful, mobile-responsive event site. I built an internal web application which helps product manager to manage client assets like photo, vedio, and other digital data. After I left, Splash engineers pushed my code to production and deployed the application.</p>

      <p>The developing environment is cakePHP a php framework. It is a MVC convention which helps engineers develop applications in the most efficient way. I used to develop app with flat php, but learned this awesome framework last summer and really appreciated the efficiency of cakePHP.</p>

      <p>Javascript is also an important part of this web application. This application loads data into part of a page without having to refresh the entire page. Managers do not have to wait for an entire page to load when they are uploading photos, vedios or updating clients' information.</p>

      <p>I implemented tons of AJAX requests and API connections with MySQL database. After server receives AJAX request, my backend functions will execute this request and return data in JSON format. Then my jQuery functions will decode JSON data into a specific format and display them on web page. The whole process is like an assemble line. Pretty Cool ha! Here is a snapshot of one of my AJAX requests.</p>

