      <p>Also, I gained lots of hands-on front end styling experience. To be honest, front end styling is a little annoying at the begining. Logic of CSS is very simple. But when you actually started using it, you will notice that there are tons of details you need to remember. But after a month of practicing, I started enjoying working with CSS and implementing these design details. I was very excited to see that my web page is getting closer and closer to the graphic design. Well, my mentor told me,<span style="text-transform: capitalize; font-weight:bold;"> Details are the product!</span></p>

